1b0e3609-610c-473c-bcf4-f6f2a51e48db.241451b6-80b9-4fb2-bd65-776956f4296b.description=
 
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
    keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable. 
    trimSpaces - If set on "true" then all the whitespaces will be removed from the value stored. 
Valid values\: true, false
Default value\: false

Returns\: 
    The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable with all whitespaces removed.

Responses\:
    isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
    notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned. 

Notes\: 
    1. If the "trimSpaces" input is set on "true" and the value from "keyName" contains only whitespaces then the response will be "isNull". 
    2. If the "trimSpaces" input is set on "false" and the value from "keyName" contains only whitespaces then the response will be "notNull". 
    3. If any other value than "true" or "false" is passed on "trimSpaces" input then the default value (false) will be used.
1b0e3609-610c-473c-bcf4-f6f2a51e48db.2fb04b9c-6a07-499c-b325-e8d304f19d5b.description=This operation runs a SQL command. Inputs\: DBServerName - The hostname or ip address of the database server. Username - The username to use when connecting to the database. Password - The password to use when connecting to the database. instance - The name instance of MSSQL Server. Leave it blank for default instance. Example\: MSSQLSERVER DbPort - The port to connect to. Default value\: 1433 Database - The name of the database. authenticationType - The type of authentication used to access the database. Valid values\: sql, windows Default value\: sql dbClass - The classname of the JDBC driver to use. dbURL - The url required to load up the driver and make your connection. Command - The command to execute. useSSL - Specifies if the communication will be encrypted using Secure Sockets Layer (SSL). Valid values\: true, false Default value\: true trustAllRoots - Specifies whether to enable weak security over SSL/TSL. A certificate is trusted even if no trusted certification authority issued it. Valid values\: true, false Default value\: false Note\: If trustAllRoots is set to 'false', a trustStore and a trustStorePassword must be provided. trustStore - The pathname of the Java TrustStore file. This contains certificates from other parties that you expect to communicate with, or from Certificate Authorities that you trust to identify other parties. If the useSSL input is set to 'false' or if trustAllRoots is 'true' this input is ignored. Format\: Java KeyStore (JKS) trustStorePassword - The password associated with the trustStore file. timeout - Seconds to wait before timing out the SQL command execution. When the default value is used, there is no limit on the amount of time allowed for a running command to complete. Default value\: 0 databasePoolingProperties - Properties for database pooling configuration. This parameter replaces the databasePooling.properties file from 9x version (you may copy-paste the file content here). Pooling is disabled by default. For more details check the /Library/Operations/Database/JDBC folder description. Example\: db.pooling.enable\=true resultSetType - the result set type. See JDBC folder description for more details. Valid values\: TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY, TYPE_SCROLL_INSENSITIVE,TYPE_SCROLL_SENSITIVE. Default value\: TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY resultSetConcurrency - the result set concurrency. See JDBC folder description for more details. Valid values\: CONCUR_READ_ONLY, CONCUR_UPDATABLE Default value\: CONCUR_READ_ONLY Results\: returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the "Command completed successfully" message if the operation succeeded, or a failure message otherwise. outputText - The return result of SQL command. updateCount - The update count of the command executed. Responses\: success - The command was executed successfully. failure - Failed to execute the command. Note\: 1. Check the JDBC folder description for details on how to load database connectors. 2. In case of using subprograms like (GET_LINE, GET_LINES, NEW_LINE, PUT, PUT_LUNE) from DBMS_OUTPUT package, the DBMS_OUTPUT.ENABLE() declaration should be used before of these calls. 1b0e3609-610c-473c-bcf4-f6f2a51e48db.468abf57-8be3-4ee4-85b9-45e6bd2fab34.description=
Generates a random number.

Inputs\:
max - The maximum number that can be returned.
min - The minimum number that can be returned.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed Successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.

Returns\:
A random number between max and min (inclusive)
1b0e3609-610c-473c-bcf4-f6f2a51e48db.483f551e-1db6-4545-877f-0dc10ddf64c3.description=
This operation does not do anything. It can be used to filter flow variables by defining them as inputs and filtering them in the Results tab.

Inputs\:
    field1 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field2 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field3 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.
    field4 – An optional input that can be used for filtering flow variables.

Results\:
    returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the value of  "field1" as it was specified at input or when filtered. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
1b0e3609-610c-473c-bcf4-f6f2a51e48db.abe53a2e-0bac-4f16-adbf-c889fae2fe74.description=
This operation waits for the number of seconds specified in the "seconds" input.

Inputs\:
    seconds - The number of seconds to wait.

Results\:
    resultString – This is the primary output. It contains the "completed sleep" message if the operation completed successfully and an error message otherwise. 

Responses\:
    success - The operation completed as stated in the description.
    failure - The operation completed unsuccessfully.

1b0e3609-610c-473c-bcf4-f6f2a51e48db.e1761994-0dee-4061-8037-8da2f1522783.description=This operation runs a SQL SELECT query. The first row is returned on the first run of the operation. Subsequent calls with the same information will return the other rows. Inputs\: DBServerName - The hostname or ip address of the database server. Username - The username to use when connecting to the server. Password - The password to use when connecting to the server. instance - The name instance of MSSQL Server. Leave it blank for default instance. Example\: MSSQLSERVER DbPort - The port to connect to. Default value\: 1433 Database - The name of the database. authenticationType - The type of authentication used to access the database. Valid values\: sql, windows default value\: sql dbClass - The class name of the JDBC driver to use. dbURL - The URL required to load up the driver and make your connection. Command - The SQL query to execute. Delimiter - The delimiter to use between resulted values in "returnResult" and column names in "columnNames". Key - The key to help keep multiple query results distinct trustAllRoots - Specifies whether to enable weak security over SSL/TSL. A certificate is trusted even if no trusted certification authority issued it. Valid values\: true, false Default value\: false Note\: If trustAllRoots is set to 'false', a trustStore and a trustStorePassword must be provided. trustStore - The pathname of the Java TrustStore file. This contains certificates from other parties that you expect to communicate with, or from Certificate Authorities that you trust to identify other parties. Format\: Java KeyStore (JKS) trustStorePassword - The password associated with the trustStore file. timeout - Seconds to wait before timing out the SQL command execution. When the default value is used, there is no limit on the amount of time allowed for a running command to complete. Default values\: 0 databasePoolingProperties - Properties for database pooling configuration. This parameter replaces the databasePooling.properties file from 9x version (you may copy-paste the file content here). Pooling is disabled by default. For more details check the /Library/Operations/Database/JDBC folder description. Example\: db.pooling.enable\=true resultSetType - the result set type. See JDBC folder description for more details. Valid values\: TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY, TYPE_SCROLL_INSENSITIVE,TYPE_SCROLL_SENSITIVE. Default value\: TYPE_SCROLL_INSENSITIVE except DB2 which is overridden to TYPE_FORWARD_ONLY resultSetConcurrency - the result set concurrency. See JDBC folder description for more details. Valid values\: CONCUR_READ_ONLY, CONCUR_UPDATABLE Default value\: CONCUR_READ_ONLY ignoreCase - If set to true the inputs' letters case will be ignored and converted to lowercase. Valid values\: true, false Default value\: true Results\: returnResult - This is the primary output. It contains the data of one row, separated by the "Delimiter". columnNames - The names of all the columns returned, separated by the "Delimiter". rowsLeft - The number of remaining rows that match the query. Responses\: more items - More rows are available for retrieval. no more items - No more rows are available. failure - Failed to execute the command. Notes\: 1. SQL statement other than SELECT statement (like INSERT, UPDATE or DELETE) is not supported. In case statements other than SELECT are executed then the operation will fail but the statements might get partially or fully executed in the database. 2. If the column type is "ntext", the "returnResult" returns the name of the JDBC driver instead of the actual column value. In this case, use the "SQL Query LOB" operation instead. Note\: Check the JDBC folder description for details on how to load database connectors. 1b0e3609-610c-473c-bcf4-f6f2a51e48db.e688b4cc-ae4f-4ed2-90a0-2c4b9197c765.description=

flow.name: Assign hostname

staticBinding.value: UPDATE hostnameDetails SET subscriptionID = '${subscriptionID}' , ipStatus = '1' , status = 'Reserved', ipAddress='${ipAddress}' where hostname = (SELECT TOP 1 hostname FROM hostnameDetails WHERE functionCode= '${functionCode}' AND country='${country}' AND locationCode='${locationCode}' AND ipStatus='0' AND status = 'Available')
SELECT Top 1 hostname from hostnameDetails WHERE subscriptionID = '${subscriptionID}' AND functionCode= '${functionCode}' AND country='${country}' AND locationCode='${locationCode}'

UPDATE hostnameDetails SET subscriptionID = '${subscriptionID}' , ipStatus = '1' , status = 'Reserved', ipAddress='${ipAddress}' where hostname = (SELECT TOP 1 hostname FROM hostnameDetails WHERE functionCode= '${functionCode}' AND country='${country}' AND locationCode='${locationCode}' AND ipStatus='0' AND status = 'Available')
